data.description: ATTENTION: Sellers are under contract for their new home and are motivated to sell NOW! In a world with few houses available it is a breath of fresh air to find a HOME in Tennessee's oldest town. Welcome home to 17 Thistledown Circle in Jonesborough. Between the hardwood floors and the tray ceilings on the main floor you will encounter plenty of warmth and splendor. Among the 3 bedrooms on this level, you will discover the deluxe primary bedroom and bath that has been updated with granite countertops and a deep soaking tub. The kitchen is enhanced by an amazing gas stove and plenty of custom cabinet space and the laundry is a breeze in the well sized utility room. The lower level provides a wealth of options for recreation, home theater, library, office, or private quarters for extended family. It also features a service area, bedroom, full bath, utility garage, and several storage areas. Once you finally want to leave the home you will step out within seconds of a walking trail that will take you to Persimmon Ridge, downtown Jonesborough, or the nearby playground. Or simply get refreshed on the spacious back deck or explore your green thumb in the garden. Let your agent know you are excited to see this home today. New roof will be installed soon. All information deemed reliable but should be verified by buyer/buyers agent.
